place.name: GREAT BIRCHAM
place.gazetteerText: BIRCHAM (Great), a parish in Docking district, Norfolk; 3 miles S of Docking, and 9 ½ W by N of Fakenham r. station. It has a post office, of the name of Bircham, under Rougham. Acres, 3,606. Real property, £2,483. Pop., 489. Houses, 86. The property mostly belongs to the Marquis of Cholmondeley. The living is a rectory in the diocese of Norwich. Value, £514.* Patron, A. Hamond, Esq. The church is good. (In 1870-72, John Marius Wilson's Imperial Gazetteer of England and Wales)
